Paterniano Del Favero
Luglio 25, 2017



Condividere













Seagate Technology PLC (NASDAQ:STX) last announced its earnings results on Wednesday, April 26th. Following the sale, the director now directly owns 11,753 shares in the company, valued at $512,783.39. Four analysts have rated the stock with a sell recommendation, nineteen have given a hold recommendation, eight have given a buy recommendation and two have assigned a strong buy recommendation to the company. Stifel Nicolaus reissued a "hold" rating and set a $45.00 target price (down from $46.00) on shares of Seagate Technology PLC in a research note on Saturday, April 29th. Over the last three months, insiders sold 116,456 shares of company stock worth $5,715,313. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Its products are designed for applications in enterprise servers and storage systems; client compute applications, where its products are designed primarily for desktop and mobile computing, and client non-compute applications, where its products are designed for a range of end user devices, such as digital video recorders (DVRs), personal data backup systems, portable external storage systems, digital media systems and surveillance systems.Covering sell-side analysts have recently weighed in on shares of Seagate Technology plc (NASDAQ:STX). The sell-side analysts are projecting earnings per share of $1.20 for the next fiscal quarter.The share price of Seagate Technology. Finally, Longbow Research upgraded Seagate Technology PLC from a neutral rating to a buy rating and increased their price target for the stock from $18.42 to $55.00 in a research report on Tuesday, April 11th. Ledyard National Bank now owns 4,255 shares of the data storage provider's stock valued at $195,000 after buying an additional 3,955 shares in the last quarter.COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: "Barclays PLC Downgrades Seagate Technology PLC (STX) to Underweight" was first reported by The Cerbat Gem and is the property of of The Cerbat Gem. Dumont & Blake Investment Advisors LLC now owns 16,163 shares of the data storage provider's stock valued at $742,000 after buying an additional 115 shares during the last quarter. If you are viewing this news story on another publication, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of USA & worldwide copyright law. Currently Seagate Technology plc (STX) has beta value of 1.72.BMO Capital Markets maintained Seagate Technology PLC (NASDAQ:STX) on Monday, July 24 with "Hold" rating.Analysts expect SJW Group (NYSE:SJW) to report $0.64 EPS on July, 26 after the close.They anticipate $0.02 EPS change or 3.03% from last quarter's $0.66 EPS. Rothschild Investment Corp IL bought a new stake in Seagate Technology PLC during the second quarter valued at $873,000. The stock's market capitalization is 11.74B.STX has been the subject of several other research reports. Going further back to the beginning of the calendar year, company shares are 3.69%. The company has a 50 day moving average of $40.54 and a 200-day moving average of $43.52. The firm had revenue of $2.67 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $2.71 billion. Needham & Company LLC boosted their price target on shares of Seagate Technology PLC from $55.00 to $57.00 and gave the stock a "strong-buy" rating in a report on Thursday, April 27th. Seagate Technology PLC had a return on equity of 79.83% and a net margin of 6.61%. Mn Services Vermogensbeheer B.V. raised its position in Seagate Technology PLC by 1.5% in the first quarter. Dumont & Blake Investment Advisors LLC raised its position in Seagate Technology PLC by 0.7% in the first quarter. During the same period a year ago, the company earned $0.22 earnings per share.The business also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Wednesday, July 5th. This dividend amount represented a yeild of $6.37. The stock now has an average rating of "Hold" and an average target price of $43.48.According to Yahoo Finance, The Dividend Date for Seagate Tech Ord Shs is Jul 5, 2017 and its Ex-Dividend Date is Jun 19, 2017."Although the near-term dynamics of technology shifts present demand variations for the storage industry from time to time, we continue to see growing storage demand in the long-run driven by the proliferation of data growth from new technologies, emerging industries, and growing businesses". Finally, Aegis assumed coverage on shares of Seagate Technology PLC in a research note on Tuesday, June 13th."As I said to someone the other day, that running a disc drive company is a little bit like driving in stop and go traffic", Luzco said in the conference call transcribed by FactSet. Institutional investors and hedge funds own 86.75% of the company's stock. In addition to HDDs, it produces a range of electronic data storage products, including solid state hybrid drives, solid state drives, peripheral component interconnect express (PCIe) cards and serial advanced technology architecture (SATA) controllers.

 




