Home / Investing / Barclays Capital reported on Seagate Technology PLC STX (NYSE:STX), lowering its target price to $40.00 today

Barclays Capital reported on Seagate Technology PLC STX (NYSE:STX), lowering its target price to $40.00 today


By Al Wild


Updated: July 26, 2017




Seagate Technology PLC STX (NYSE:STX) had its target price lowered to $40.00 by Barclays Capital in a report released Thursday July 13, 2017.  The new target price indicates a possible upside of 0.04% based on  the company's last stock close price.
Previously on 6/16/2017, Evercore ISI reported about Seagate Technology PLC STX (NYSE:STX) raised the target price from $0.00 to $48.00.  At the time, this indicated a possible upside of 0.15%.
Yesterday Seagate Technology PLC STX (NYSE:STX) traded -2.59% lower at $38.50.  The company‚Äôs 50-day moving average is $40.54 and its 200-day moving average is $43.52.  The last stock close price is down -25.69% from the 200-day moving average, compared to the S&P 500 which has increased 0.06% over the same time.  12,621,492 shares of the stock were exchanged, up from an average trading volume of 5,015,000 
See Chart Below

Seagate Technology PLC STX has a 52 week low of $30.09 and a 52 week high of $50.96 with a P/E ratio of 13.31  The company‚Äôs market cap is currently $0.
In addition to Barclays Capital reporting its target price, a total of 25 firms have reported on the stock.  The consensus target price is $27.84 with 4 firms rating the stock a strong buy, 4 firms rating the stock a buy, 20 firms rating the stock a hold, 3 firms rating the stock a underperform, and finally 1 firm rating the stock a sell.
About Seagate Technology PLC STX (NYSE:STX)
Seagate Technology public limited company is a provider of electronic data storage technology and solutions. The Company's principal products are hard disk drives (HDDs). In addition to HDDs, it produces a range of electronic data storage products, including solid state hybrid drives, solid state drives, peripheral component interconnect express (PCIe) cards and serial advanced technology architecture (SATA) controllers. Its storage technology portfolio also includes storage subsystems and high performance computing solutions. Its products are designed for applications in enterprise servers and storage systems, client compute applications and client non-compute applications. It designs, fabricates and assembles various components found in its disk drives, including read/write heads and recording media. Its design and manufacturing operations are based on technology platforms that are used to produce various disk drive products that serve multiple data storage applications and markets.

