Business   Investors Focused Movers: Maxim Integrated Products, Inc. (MXIM), Seagate Technology plc (STX)
Business
Investors Focused Movers: Maxim Integrated Products, Inc. (MXIM), Seagate Technology plc (STX)By Martin Almanza - July 24, 201701
Share on Facebook
Tweet on Twitter



 Maxim Integrated Products, Inc. (MXIM) closed business day at $45.10 with -5.73%. The firm exchanged a volume of 7.63 million shares at hands. In contrast, the average volume was 2.2 million shares. At the time of writing, Shares the company recently traded 21.07% away 52-week low and noted price movement -9.26% away from the 52-week high level. Many investors will opt to use multiple time periods when examining moving averages. Investors may also be paying close concentration to some simple moving average indicators on shares of Maxim Integrated Products, Inc. (MXIM). The moving average uses the sum of all of the previous closing prices over a certain time period and divides the result by the number of prices used in the calculation. Recently, the stock has been noticed trading -1.73% away from the 20-day moving average. Going toward to the 50-day, we can see that shares are currently trading -3.27% off of that figure. Zooming out to the 200-day moving average, shares have been seen trading 4.36% away from that value. The Stock currently has a consensus recommendation of 2.60. This rating uses a scale from 1 to 5. A recommendation of 1 or 2 would represent a consensus Buy. A rating of 4 or 5 would indicate a consensus Sell. A rating of 3 would signify a consensus Hold recommendation. Investors who are keeping close eye on Maxim Integrated Products, Inc. (MXIM) stock; watched recent volatility movements, they can see that shares have been recorded at 1.98% for the week, and 1.79% for the last month. Taking a look back at some historical performance numbers for Maxim Integrated Products, Inc. (MXIM), we can see that the stock moved -4.25% for the last five trades. For the last month, company shares are -1.98%. For the last quarter, the stock has performed 0.40%. Over the past full-year, shares have performed 19.60%. If we look back year-to-date, the stock has performed 16.93%.Shares of the company have shown an EPS growth of 10.90% in the last 5 years. Its sales stood at -0.90% a year on average in the period of last five years. The company maintains price to book ratio of 5.79. A P/B ratio of less than 1.0 can indicate that a stock is undervalued, while a ratio of greater than 1.0 may indicate that a stock is overvalued. The company was able to keep return on investment at 15.30% in the last twelve months. Seagate Technology plc (STX) climbed 0.41% and its total traded volume was 3.26 million shares contrast to the average volume of 5.02 million shares. The stock closed its day at $39.58. The closing price represents the final price that a stock is traded for on a trading day. It‚Äôs the most up-to-date valuation until trading begins again on the next day. However, most financial instruments are traded after hours which mean that the closing price of a stock might not match the after-hours price. Regardless, closing prices are a useful tool that investors use to quantify changes in stock prices over time. The closing prices are compared day-by-day to look for trends and can measure market sentiment for any security over the course of a trading day. The company maintained ROI for the last twelve months at 7.40%. The stock has a beta value of 1.72. Beta can be useful to gauge stock price volatility in relation to the broader market. For the past 5 years, the stock‚Äôs EPS growth has been nearly -5.60%. Seagate Technology plc (STX) observed trading 0.37% away from the 20-day moving average and -4.04% off from its 50-day simple moving average. Recently, the stock has been moved -4.84% from its 200-day simple moving average. The institutional ownership stake in the corporation is 91.70%. Its revenue has grown at an average annualized rate of about 0.30% during the past five years. Its RSI (Relative Strength Index) reached 48.23. The debt-to-equity ratio (D/E) was recorded at 3.25. However its weekly volatility is 1.72% and monthly volatility is 2.66%. Let‚Äôs take a gaze at how the stock has been performing recently. Seagate Technology plc (STX) shares have moved 0.20% in the week and -4.99% in the month. Year to date is 3.69%, -17.99% over the last quarter, 8.53% for the past six months and 26.78% over the last 12 months. The average analysts gave this company a mean recommendation of 2.80. A rating of less than 2 means buy, ‚Äúhold‚Äù within the 3 range, ‚Äúsell‚Äù within the 4 range, and ‚Äústrong sell‚Äù within the 5 range. RELATED ARTICLESMORE FROM AUTHORStocks within Investor Screening: Brocade Communications Systems, Inc. (BRCD) closed Friday at $12.63 with 0.00%, Rio Tinto plc (RIO)Stocks within Investor Screening: Gentex Corporation (GNTX) closed Friday at $17.28 with -7.40%, Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Limited (TEVA)Investors Focused Movers: Nabors Industries Ltd. (NBR), ViewRay, Inc. (VRAY)

